	heroObjectPosition={`center center`}
	directAnswerHtml={`<strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">If you're in college, the Father's Heart Bible™ is for you.</strong> You're figuring out who you are away from home — carrying anxiety, all-nighters, loneliness in a crowd, money stress, and maybe a faith that feels shakier than it did in high school. The <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Father's Heart Bible™</a> is a fresh English translation you can read and <em>listen to</em> free on your phone, between classes or at 2am — and it reveals God as <em>Father</em> from Genesis to Revelation. Whether you searched "Bible verses for college students," "verses for anxiety," or "is God still there when I doubt," it starts in one place: before you achieve anything, you are already His.`}
	keyTakeaway={`In the freedom and the fog of college, your identity isn't your major, your grades, your relationship status, or your doubts. You belong to a Father who hasn't let go — and you can always come home to Him.`}
	painsHeading={`What college students are carrying`}
	painsIntroHtml={`College can be the best years and the hardest years at the same time. Behind the highlight reels and the late nights is a generation under real strain — anxious, lonely, stretched thin, and quietly wondering where God fits now that home is far away. The numbers tell the truth most students feel but rarely say out loud.`}
	painStats={[
		{ value: `35%`, label: `of college students have been diagnosed with anxiety; 27% report depression (American College Health Association)` },
		{ value: `57%`, label: `of college students say they feel lonely — and most never say it out loud` },
		{ value: `66%`, label: `of young people raised in church walk away from their faith during college (Lifeway Research)` },
		{ value: `68%`, label: `of students say mental or emotional struggles hurt their academic performance in the last month` },
		{ value: `20%`, label: `are experiencing serious psychological distress right now (ACHA, Fall 2024)` },
		{ value: `4x`, label: `students who feel lonely are over four times more likely to experience severe distress` },
