	aFatherHeading={`A Father for college students`}
	aFatherBodyHtml={`<p>The answer to the anxiety, the loneliness, and the late-night questions isn't a better planner, a thicker skin, or pretending you've got it together. The answer is a <strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">Father</strong> — a real, present, perfect Father for a beloved child who's a long way from home.</p><p>Here's what nobody put on the campus tour: you can build the resume, get the grades, find the relationship, and still feel like you're disappearing. Because the deepest thing in you isn't asking <em>am I successful?</em> It's asking <em>am I loved? do I belong? does anyone delight in me, even here?</em> And the answer is yes — louder than the comparison, the pressure, and the voices online.</p><p>Your heavenly Father isn't waiting at the finish line for you to earn your way back. He's the kind of Father who sees you while you're still a long way off, and runs. Your major doesn't impress Him and your doubts don't scare Him. You are His — before you achieve, before you measure up, before you figure any of it out. And He is a Father you can always come home to.</p>`}
