	voicesHeading={`The Father's heart, in their words`}
	voicesIntroHtml={`Away from home for the first time, it's easy to wonder who you are when no one's watching. The truth beneath every verse here — that you are first and forever a loved child — is the one these voices gave their lives to:`}
	voices={[
		{ quote: `There is heaven in the depth of that word — Father.`, name: `Charles Spurgeon`, role: `the “Prince of Preachers”`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/e48a128da123135241be9c95cf35b37498d94ea5-500x617.jpg` },
		{ quote: `God tenderly invites us to believe that He is our true Father and we are His true children.`, name: `Martin Luther`, role: `the Reformer, on the opening words of the Lord's Prayer`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/b205722e3e040337b10b11b66e159abd8623472e-500x791.jpg` },
		{ quote: `The hardest, gladdest thing in the world is, to cry Father! from a full heart.`, name: `George MacDonald`, role: `who taught that the Fatherhood of God is the heart of the gospel`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/35e71c2610893383d20b60883aa0b1d4d4664cbc-500x726.jpg` },
	]}
	voicesCreditHtml={`Photos via <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Wikimedia Commons</a> &mdash; Charles Spurgeon, Martin Luther, and George MacDonald (all public domain).`}
	wordHeading={`His Word will not return void`}
	wordBodyHtml={`<p>You may walk through seasons of college where God feels distant, where faith is more questions than answers. That's okay. The seed of His Word, planted in you now, doesn't expire when you doubt — it waits, and it works. A Father this patient is not letting go of you while you find your way.</p><p class="mt-4" style="color: var(--color-ink);">"My word… will not return to me empty, but will accomplish that which I purpose." <span style="color: var(--color-muted);">— Isaiah 55:11</span></p>`}
	fatherSaysHeading={`What the Father says over you`}
	fatherSaysHtml={`<p>"You're far from home now, but you've never been far from Me. I was there in the dorm room the first homesick night, and I'm here in the library at 2am. I'm not grading you. I'm not waiting for you to get it all right before I'll come close.</p><p>You don't have to have it figured out — your major, your future, your faith. Bring Me the questions; I'm not afraid of them. When you feel invisible in a room full of people, know this: I see you. I know your name. I made you fearfully and wonderfully, on purpose, and I delight in you — not for your grades or your follows or who you're dating, but because you are Mine. Wander if you must. I'll be watching the road, and when you turn toward home, I will run. There is nothing — nothing — that can separate you from My love. I am your Father, and I've got you."</p>`}
	prayerHeading={`A prayer for college students`}
	prayerHtml={`<p>Our Father, we thank You and praise You for these college students. Let them hear Your whisper above all the noise — the comparison, the pressure to perform, the voices online telling them they're not enough. Let them encounter Your love — not as a rule, but as a Father's delight — and know they are Your beloved, apart from their grades, their resume, or their relationship status.</p><p>Give them grace to receive their identity from You before the world and the campus tell them who to be. Father, meet them in the loneliness of a crowded room and in the fog of not yet knowing who they are; be their home when home is far away, and hold their faith steady through every honest question and every season of doubt.</p><p>I pray Your protection over them from the enemy, from temptation, from isolation and the lie that they have to carry it alone, and from despair. Let them know there is no condemnation in You, that they are fearfully and wonderfully made, and that nothing can separate them from Your love. Let them know You, their Father, as their true home and reward. And may they wake up every single day knowing they are loved by their heavenly Father.</p><p>In Jesus' name, amen.</p>`}
